    <string-array name="help_topics_text">
        <item>Entering the player number is now a separate step.</item>
        <item>When you enter a try, the conversion kick clock starts. When you add a penalty, the
            PK clock starts. The kick clock closes automatically when the time is up. You can tap
            the clock to confirm success or miss.</item>
        <item>Connection to the Rugby Referee Watch app on your phone works via Bluetooth. You do
            need to approve permission.</item>
        <item>In the settings you can select the standard match types. If you want to change
            anything (like duration), tap \'Match type details\'. Do this in the phone app to store
            your custom match type.</item>
        <item>Looking for penalty try? Check under foul play.</item>
        <item>During a game, swipe back to open the correction screen. On this screen you can tap
            the event you want to undo, or redo.</item>
        <item>Before the game starts you can set which team will kick off by tapping the home or
            away team score.</item>
        <item>Screen on is a very useful setting to keep the screen on during a game, but this will
            use more battery. Consider switching off Wifi, GPS and Bluetooth during a game, this
            app does not use these during the game.</item>
        <item>Matches will be stored on the watch for 30 days, use the companion app on your phone
            to download them.</item>
        <item>From the settings you can open this screen. Find support contacts in the App Store
            for more help.</item>
    </string-array>

